msContents.summary: Fragment of an Abbasid Qur'ān probably written in the third or fourth century H. / ninth or tenth century C.E, containing verses 19-34 from Sura al-Muʾminūn (سورة المؤمنون), the complete Sura al-Furqān (سورة الفرقان), Sura al-Shuʿarāʾ (سورة الشعراء), Sura al-Naml (سورة النمل) , Sura al-Qaṣaṣ (سورة القصص), Sura al-,Ankabūt (سورة العنكبوت), verses 17-60 from Sura al-Rūm (سورة الروم), te complete Sura Luqmān (سورة لقمان), and verses 1-6 from Sura al-Sajda (سورة السجدة) . Folios 2-10 and 44 are missing.

msItem.title: Sura al-Furqān: seventy-seven verses (سورة الفرقان سبعون وسبع اية) [line 17]
Sura al-Shuʿarāʾ: two hundred and twenty-seven verses (سورة الشعراء مائتان وعشرون وسبع ايات) [line 13]
Sura Ṭs al-Naml: ninety-five verses (سورة النمل تسعون وخمس اية) [line 2]
Sura Ṭāʾ-Sīn-Mīm (i.e. al-Qaṣāṣ): eighty-eight verses (سورة طسم ثمانون وثمان ايات) [line 16]
Sura al-ʿAnkabūt: sixty-nine verses (سورة العنكبوت تسع وستون اية) [line 12]
Sura al-Rūm: sixty verses (سورة الروم ستون اية) [line 18]
Sura Luqmān: thirty-three verses (سورة لقمان ثلثون وثلاث ايات) [line 3]
Sura al-Sajda: thirty verses (سورة السجدة ثلثون اية) [line 4]

handNote.p: The script seems to correspond to the Abbasid Style C II as described by François Deroche.

origin.origDate: 10th or 11th century AD /4th or 5th century Hijri

history.provenance: Bought from Professor E.H. Palmer Palmer, Edward Henry, 1840-1882 and E.E. Tyrwhitt Drake Tyrwhitt Drake, E.E. in 1878.
